OL,6,FThe government has ordered an inquiry
OL,7,Fand the Department for Education
OL,8,F(DfE) has apologised after it
OL,9,Fmiscalculated its funding plans for
OL,10,Fthe next academic year.
OL,12,FThe DfE's top official, permanent
OL,13,Fsecretary Susan Acland-Hood, said in
OL,14,Fa letter to the Parliamentary
OL,15,FEducation Select Committee the number
OL,16,Fof pupils was underestimated, with a
OL,17,Fplanned 2.7% increase per pupil for
OL,18,F2024/25 subsequently revised to 1.9%.
OL,3,CFormal review ordered after DfE
OL,4,Capologises for schools funding error
